snippet.textDisplay: I'm almost positive that it's Maddox at the end and beginning of the MV. Maddox had been narrating the Intro: Long Journey and Outro: Long Journey aswell. Through the whole journey of the real ateez battling the dark ateez, Maddox was just merely a spectator, narrating for us in the into and outro. At the end of the MV, the same dining room both sides of ATEEZ were in is all damaged and left behind dark and chaotically after the two sides had come to an agreement at the dining table to fight for the last time. Maddox walks around there after the fight, as he had been the spectator, narrating. Their MV's aren't in chronological order of their storyline anyways. The only thing I'll tell you is that 'Wave' is at the end of the timeline, and to cut a long ass story short: real ATEEZ has won. If you need more explanation, look up some theories :) So, I think it's Maddox and the 'real ATEEZ' won the last fight against their alter egos.
